rew McDonald (water polo)|Drew McDonald]], [[Kevin Robertson]], [[Peter Schnugg]], [[Terry Schroeder]], [[John Siman]], [[Jon Svendsen]], [[Joseph Vargas|Joe Vargas]]. Head coach: [[Monte Nitzkowski]].<ref name=\"Olympians\"/>\n\n* {{flagicon|USA}} [[Water polo at the 1984 Summer Olympics|1984 Los Angeles]] \u2013 '''{{Silver2}} Silver medal'''\n*: [[Craig Wilson (water polo)|Craig Wilson]] <small>(GK)</small>, [[Kevin Robertson]], [[Gary Figueroa]], [[Peter Campbell (water polo)|Peter Campbell]], [[Doug Burke (water polo)|Doug Burke]], [[Joseph Vargas|Joe Vargas]], [[Jon Svendsen]], [[John Siman]], [[Andrew McDonald (water polo)|Drew McDonald]], [[Terry Schroeder]] <small>(C)</small>, [[Jody Campbell]], [[Tim Shaw (swimmer)|Tim Shaw]], [[Christopher Dorst|Chris Dorst]] <small>(GK)</small>. Head coach: [[Monte Nitzkowski]].<ref name=\"1984OG\"/><ref name=\"1984OG PDF\"/><ref name=\"1984OG SR\"/>\n\n* {{flagicon|KOR}} [[Water polo at the 1988 Summer Olympics|1988 Seoul]] \u2013 '''{{Silver2}} Silver medal'''\n*: [[Craig Wilson (water polo)|Craig Wilson]] <small>(GK)</small>, [[Kevin Robertson]], [[James Bergeson]], [[Peter Campbell (water polo)|Peter Campbell]], [[Douglas Kimbell|Doug Kimbell]], [[Craig Klass]], [[Alan Mouchawar]], [[Jeffrey Campbell (water polo)|Jeff Campbell]], [[Greg Boyer (water polo)|Greg Boyer]], [[Terry Schroeder]] <small>(C)</small>, [[Jody Campbell]], [[Christopher Duplanty|Chris Duplanty]] <small>(GK)</small>, [[Michael Evans (water polo)|Mike Evans]]. Head coach: [[Bill Barnett (water polo)|Bill Barnett]].<ref name=\"1988OG\"/><ref name=\"1988OG PDF\"/><ref name=\"1988OG SR\"/>\n\n* {{flagicon|ESP}} [[Water polo at the 1992 Summer Olympics|1992 Barcelona]] \u2013 4th place\n*: [[Craig Wilson (water polo)|Craig Wilson]] <small>(GK)</small>, [[John Vargas (water polo)|John Vargas]], [[Christopher Duplanty|Chris Duplanty]] <small>(GK)</small>, [[Michael Evans (water polo)|Mike Evans]], [[Douglas Kimbell|Doug Kimbell]], [[Charles Harris (water